# Deno TypeScript Personal Data Backup Scripts

Runtime: Deno 2

## Project Overview
Cross-platform TypeScript backup scripts for macOS, Linux, and Windows personal data management.

## Backup Data Types
- Home directories: App, DEV, Note, Course, Media, Work, etc.
- System configurations:
  - NixOS config files
  - macOS Homebrew files
  - Linux sysctl configurations (/etc/sysctl.d/99-sysctl.conf)
  - ...
- Application data:
  - Unix: ~/.config/ (zed, fish, fontconfig, rustdesk, maa, ...)
  - Windows: AppData/Roaming/
  - Cross-platform: SSH keys (~/.ssh), etc.

## Backup Task Types

### 7z Type
- Compresses directories/files into 7zip archives when dest ends with '.7z'
- Platform commands:
  - Linux/Windows: 7z
  - macOS: 7zz
- Example: { path: "~/DEV", dest: "DEV.7z" }

### dir Type
- Direct copy without compression
- Example: { path: "~/Media", dest: "Media" }

### task Type
- Executes custom TypeScript functions
- Structure: { type: "task", backup: Function, restore?: Function }

## Key Features
- OS filtering: Tasks filtered by os property (linux | darwin | windows | nixos | archlinux | any)
- Before callbacks: Pre-processing functions
  - Cleanup: Removes target/, node_modules/, .astro/, .react-router/, etc. before compression
  - NixOS config backup
  - .DS_Store removal
  - ...
- Platform-specific handling: Different logic for each OS type
